{
  "blockers": [
    {
      "id": "B-001",
      "section": "Lease And Safety Invariants / Implementation Steps step 4",
      "issue": "Claim-time soul snapshot semantics are ambiguous in two load-bearing ways. (1) The spec asserts that `ClaimNextRun` writes soul provenance to `task_runs.metadata_json` and that the active digest is snapshotted 'again at task-run claim time' (ADR-003), but never names *whose* soul is captured: the claiming session's existing `soul_snapshot_id`, the agent definition resolved fresh from disk, or some other source. (2) It does not say whether `ClaimNextRun` performs file I/O / validation / digest computation inside the claim transaction (which runs under `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` per L-003) or merely copies a precomputed digest from the session row. Resolving `SOUL.md` from inside the only authoritative claim primitive risks turning a hot-path atomic transition into a slow, fail-prone, FS-bound operation, and risks splitting claim semantics for runs that have no parent session (scheduler-created or orphan-recovered).",
      "rationale": "L-003 and L-005: `ClaimNextRun` is the exclusive authority for the claim transition, must serialize via `BEGIN IMMEDIATE`, and may not depend on second sources of truth. L-001 reinforces that work performed inside a request/transaction lifetime cannot be tied to long-running file I/O. Any spec change touching this primitive must be precise about what it is and is not allowed to do.",
