      "id": "B-003",
      "section": "Data Models",
      "issue": "The spec says 'Add a numbered SQLite migration' but never names the target database (`agh.db`, `events.db`, the catalog databases, automation scheduler state). It also adds two columns to the existing `sessions` table without specifying which migration registry owns the alteration. L-008 was a Critical CodeRabbit incident precisely because two schema paths (real migrations vs `EnsureSchema`) drifted; the Agent Soul spec must pick one, name it, and specify it.",
