      "section": "API Endpoints — POST /api/sessions/{session_id}/soul/refresh",
      "issue": "Refresh re-resolves `SOUL.md`, validates it, computes a digest, opens the snapshot store, possibly writes a new snapshot, updates the session row, and emits an audit event. None of this is bounded by the request lifetime spec, and the spec does not say whether the work runs under `c.Request.Context()` or detached. If the client disconnects mid-refresh, the session row may be left in a half-updated state.",
      "rationale": "L-001: any work that outlives an HTTP/UDS request must detach via `context.WithoutCancel(ctx)`. The spec inherits the same risk class as the prompt-stream-stall incident: tying long-running runtime mutation to a request context. The 409-on-active-task-run rule is necessary but not sufficient — refresh on an idle session can still race a fresh claim arriving mid-flight.",
